<br>
If the highest possible available AC was 750 AC, you would indeed have hit the soft cap at 600 AC, would you have not?  You increase it by 150 AC and see no difference.  Its not possible to increase it further (in this theoretical discussion) therefore for you and your circumstances, the AC soft cap is 600 AC.<br>
<br>
If it was possible to endlessly add AC, test the impact, then add or decrease it, we'd be in a better position to be sure.  However, from the evidence so far presented, there is a definite point at which adding additional AC to the maximum possible AC attainable by the testers does not seem to give added benefits.  We can only theorize that continuing to add additional AC might eventually show more benefits.<br>
<br>
So, if you have 1250 AC and you will see no further benefits until you get to 1800 AC and getting 1800 AC is completely <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>impossible</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for you to get, then your effective soft cap is 1250.<br>
<br>
