If you use measure tank quality by DPS taken, all the evidence suggests that it would make a difference (though obviously I haven't parsed that particular example, because you only just made it up). You don't hit the theoretical max for mitigation (everything mitigated to minimum damage) against anything except a level 1 mob.<br>
<br>
If your criteria is 'I can tank it well enough, who cares', then anything over a few hundred AC is indistinguishable from 1800AC.<br>
